Citation.sTitle: Conductivity of Some Molten Chlorides at Elevated Temperatures I. Experimental and Calculation Techniques for BeCl2, ZnCl2, and PbCl2
Citation.sAbstract: A cell for the electrical conductivity measurements of molten salts at the elevated temperatures and vapor pressures of several tens of atmospheres was constructed. The electrical conductivities of molten BeCl2, ZnCl2, and PbCl2 were measured up to temperatures of (823, 1421, and 1320) K, respectively. The melts density was estimated, and molar conductivities at the same temperatures were calculated.
